===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[ornament]] such as a [[garland]] or chain which hangs loosely from two tacked spots.
# {{context|architecture|lang=en}} A [[bas-relief]], [[painting]], or structural [[motif]] resembling such an ornament.
#*{{quote-book|year=1963|author={{w|Margery Allingham}}
|title={{w|The China Governess}}
|chapter=1|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL2004261W
|passage=The half-dozen pieces {{...}} were painted white and carved with '''festoons''' of flowers, birds and cupids. To display them the walls had been tinted a vivid blue which had now faded, but the carpet, which had evidently been stored and recently relaid, retained its original turquoise.}}
# A raised [[cable]] with light globes attached.
# {{context|astronomy|lang=en}} A cloud on [[Jupiter]] that hangs out of its home belt or zone into an adjacent area forming a curved finger-like image or a complete loop back to its home belt or zone.
# {{context|entomology|lang=en}} Any of a series of [[wrinkle]]s on the backs of some [[tick]]s.
# {{context|technology|lang=en}} A specific style of electric [[light bulb]] consisting of a cylindrical enclosure with two points of contact on either end providing power to the [[filament]] or [[diode]].

